<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1686,2035]" pageId="7" pageNumber="386">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1686,1711]" pageId="7" pageNumber="386">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennae with ten or eleven segments. Tenth tergite widely emarginated, latero-distal portion that connects with cercus armed with denticulate tubercule and sclerotized. Cerci curving inwards medially, apex truncated and armed with small dorso-apical prolongation.
</paragraph>
